resources.materials

Class Material

  • java.lang.Object
    • resources.materials.Material

  • public class Material
extends java.lang.Object
    Material for Splines and Meshes. It can work together with any kind of Renderers, you should only store the required slots in it. Note that not all Rendeers support all types of slots, but that isn't a problem if you add unsupported type of slot to a Material, the Renderer will ignore it. If you don't add a slot which is requred by a built-in Renderer, it will use some kind of a default value.

      • getSlot

        @Nullable
public MaterialSlot getSlot(@NotNull
                                       java.lang.String key)
        Returns the Material's specified slot. If you use your own Renderer, you can use any String key you want. However if you use the built-in Renderers, you should use these Renderers' specified keys. You can reach these keys as this Material class's static final String values. Note that not all Rendeers support all types of slots, but that isn't a problem if you add unsupported type of slot to a Material, the Renderer will ignore it. If you don't add a slot which is requred by a built-in Renderer, it will use some kind of a default value.
